      "summary": "New Zealand deployed a compact 4-2-3-1 low/mid-block (26% low block, 16% mid block phases), conceding 50.1% possession and relying on limited counter-attacks. Despite the tactical structure, Belgium's 3.99 xG exposed NZL's inability to contain their final-third entries (203 BEL receptions). JUST provided the only genuine attacking outlet, scoring at 83' to make it 5-1. CROCOMBE kept the deficit from being worse with 5 saves.",
